.TH "usb_hub_set_port_power" 9 "usb_hub_set_port_power" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_hub_set_port_power \- control hub port's power state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb_hub_set_port_power
.BI "(struct usb_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "struct usb_hub *hub "  ","
.BI "int port1 "  ","
.BI "bool set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
USB device belonging to the usb hub
.IP "hub" 12
target hub
.IP "port1" 12
port index
.IP "set" 12
expected status
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
call this function to control port's power via setting or
clearing the port's PORT_POWER feature.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful. A negative error code otherwise.
